                "name": "Don Welty",
                "href": "/profile/Don-Welty"
            },
            "answer_text": "Instead of \u201cin this essay, I discuss . . . .\u201d It is probably better not to use that as a part of your essay. Whether you state your thesis or not, you should have a thesis statement, which would tell the reader your opinion of the topic. Look up essay writing or thesis statements on the internet. UNC has a writing clinic with a lot of well-written information on various aspects of writing. A thesis statement is a statement about the topic you want to write about. Many writers suggest a 3-part introduction consisting of some preliminary sentencesa thesis statementan description of the topics you are going to discuss.If you use this format, you will never say \u201cIn this essay, I discuss. . . .\u201d For example\u2014 Pearl Harbor was a was a great victory for the Japanese and a total disaster for the United States. (Preliminary) However, it was a tactical victory but a strategic failure and a disaster for the Japanese. (Thesis) Three aspects of the attack doomed the Japanese: (1) The attack angered the American population as nothing else could. (2) The aircraft carriers were not in Pearl Harbor when the attack took place. (3) Fuel and repair facilities were untouched. (Topics in the organization) ",
