                "name": "Gaurav Verma",
                "href": "/profile/Gaurav-Verma-219"
            },
            "answer_text": "While writing any type of essay, you will have to address the contents discussed in the essay. This is usually done in the introduction of the essay, where the author explains the topics that are covered in the essay and their significance. Apart from this, you may also find the need to address the contents of your essay in the body section and the conclusion of the essay. Although the need to address the essay contents in the body section is somewhat unusual, however in the conclusion, the author brings together all the points discussed in the essay and initiates the sentence as \u201cThis essay has discussed\u2026\u201d In either of the cases, it is important that you get the right essay writing help, either form your colleagues or on the internet to understand the various different ways in which you can frame the \u201cIn this essay we will discuss...\u201d sentence. It mainly comes down to your proficiency as a writer, using which you can come up with different ways to frame the sentence such as, \u201cOne of the main topic of this essay is\u2026\u201d or \u201cThe following paragraphs of this essay will discuss\u2026\u201d etc. There are a lot of different possibilities and sentence structures which you can play with. As an additional tip, you can try reading the introduction section of different essay and get a better idea of how different authors frame this sentence as per the nature of their particular essays. ",
