            "author_info": {
                "name": "Robert Charles Lee",
                "href": "/profile/Robert-Charles-Lee"
            },
            "answer_text": "Here\u2019s an old schoolboy trick from my schooldays over 40 years to get the schoolmaster\u2019s attention:\u2014 \u201cThis essay demonstrates the truth of The Merchant of Venice by William Shakespeare being penned by no other than the 6th Viscount of Islingbobblewarble.\u201dThis answer demonstrates one alternative opening among many others you will receive for this question. All present and future answers will demonstrate that you have to sit down, have a nice cup of tea, and some snacks too, and then in a good mood try to come up with alternative phraseology to demonstrate your knowledge of the subject matter. Protip:\u2014 In any kind of extended writing (such as essays), avoid using words like I and you (and probably also we, but not he, she, it, they, etc). Get straight into the game. Avoid telling the reader you will do something. Tell the reader this thing will show XYZ is this, that or the other. ",
