                "href": "/profile/Aaron-Lawler-2"
            },
            "answer_text": "The reason we use these kinds of statements is to open dialogue with reader quickly and preview the writing. Although, less elegant this is the quickest way to do this and is why it has become cliche (and ironically less interesting, thus less effective). Alternatives include \u201c\"In this discourse..,\u201d or \u201c\"In this report\u2026\u201d yet these are equally disinteresting. Instead consider being specific. \u201c\"In review of the factors which led to the escalation of the 1812 War, three stand out for their particular impact; and it is those three factors which one could reasonably argue shaped early US history.\u201d ",
