            "answer_text": "When possible, make the statement (usually thesis) without using \u201cthis essay\u2026\u201d as a lead in. For example, if you were going to write: \u201cIn this essay, I will discuss why I think apples are better than oranges,\u201d you should probably instead write \u201cApples are better than oranges.\u201d The readers already know it is an essay. They should expect an argument, comparison, or some in depth exploration of a topic. ",
