            "answer_text": "There is nothing actually wrong with writing \"In this essay/paper/report I will/shall discuss/compare/evaluate \u2026\" It\u2019s not the most captivating way to write a thesis statement, but it does the job. I prefer \u201cpaper\u201d to \u201cessay\u201d, and so, it seems, do most academics; Google Scholar gives 10,600 results for \u201cIn this paper, I will discuss\u201d as opposed to a mere 1,800 for \u201cIn this essay, I will discuss.\u201d (These examples are probably essays in a collection rather than the kind of essays submitted by students.) On the other hand, a simple \u201cI will discuss\u201d gets a whopping 347,000 hits, so it may be best to just drop the \u201cin this essay\u201d altogether. ",
