            "answer_text": "The first sentence or two of an essay is intended to catch people\u2019s attention. Do something that catches attention. Sometimes, asking a question is appropriate, sometimes making a bold statement is appropriate. Imagine your essay is a video on YouTube. Your first sentence is the thumbnail and title. It\u2019s got to catch the eye. For example, if you\u2019re talking about a river that was polluted, you might say, Last week, twenty-three fish were found dead on the edge of the river. Amazingly enough, that\u2019s fewer than any single week in the last six months. \u2026 And you\u2019re off. ",
